// FAQ Questions and Answers
"help_faq_q1" = "How do I register my pet?";
"help_faq_a1" = "You can register your pet in the 'My Pets' menu by tapping 'Add New Pet'. Fill in the required information and upload one or more photos.";
"help_faq_q2" = "What information should I provide in my pet's profile?";
"help_faq_a2" = "You already provided your pet's name when ordering the tag, and it will appear in your pet's profile once the tag is activated. Enter your pet's species and breed. To prevent misuse, these details can only be entered once. If you make a mistake or a typo, contact us and we'll help. Here you can also add your cat/dog's weight, age, colour, and any distinctive features or typical behaviour. You can upload photos too. These can help with quick identification and safe return of your pet. You decide what information is visible about your pet if they go missing.";
"help_faq_q3" = "How does the QR code tag work?";
"help_faq_a3" = "Every pet receives a unique QR code tag. This code is linked to your pet's profile. When someone scans the QR code with their phone, they can instantly view your pet's profile and the contact details you've marked as public.";
"help_faq_q4" = "Can I update my pet's details later?";
"help_faq_a4" = "Yes! You can update your pet's details anytime in the 'My Pets' section by selecting your pet and tapping 'Edit Profile'. You can update any field except name, species, and breed, including photos. Changes are saved immediately.";
"help_faq_q5" = "How do I order a replacement tag?";
"help_faq_a5" = "Go to the 'Home/My Account' page and tap 'Order Replacement Tag'. Select which pet needs a new tag. Replacement eligibility depends on your Senra account; visit senra.pet for details.";
"help_faq_q6" = "How do I activate my tag after it arrives?";
"help_faq_a6" = "Download the SENRA mobile app from the Google Play Store or App Store! Open it and go to the 'Activate' menu, point your phone's camera at the QR code on the tag! Scanning the QR code links the tag to your account. Then you need to select your existing pet or create a new profile.";
"help_faq_q7" = "Can I give a SENRA tag as a gift?";
"help_faq_a7" = "Yes! SENRA tags make great gifts for pet owners. Simply order the tag from your own account — when the recipient receives it, they can scan the QR code, create their own account, and activate the tag for their pet. The recipient doesn't need to register in advance — scanning the tag guides them through account creation and linking the tag to their pet.";
"help_faq_q8" = "What should I do if my pet goes missing?";
"help_faq_a8" = "Go to 'My Pets', tap the menu on your pet's card, and select 'Mark as Missing'. This creates a 'missing pet alert' that is sent to all SENRA community members registered within 10 km of your address. Vets and shelters are also notified. People nearby can see the alert and notify you if they've seen or found your pet (directly or through our online system). You'll receive an instant notification for every sighting.";
"help_faq_q9" = "How do missing pet alerts work?";
"help_faq_a9" = "When you mark your cat or dog as missing, an alert is created with your pet's photo and details. SENRA users within 10 km are immediately notified about your missing pet, and your pet also appears on the 'Missing Pets' map. Vets and shelters registered in the SENRA system in your area also receive the alert. Anyone who scans your pet's tag can send you the location where they found them and their own contact details. They can also contact you directly if you've made your contact information public in your profile.";
"help_faq_q10" = "How do I order a replacement tag?";
"help_faq_a10" = "Go to the 'Home/My Account' page and tap 'Order Replacement Tag'. Select which pet needs a new tag. Maximum and Standard plan subscribers can request free replacement tags, while Starter plan members can order replacements for the shipping cost.";
"help_faq_q11" = "What is the referral programme?";
"help_faq_a11" = "Choose your personal Referral Code from My Pets. Share it with friends and family. When someone uses your code and subscribes to a paid plan (Standard or Maximum), both you and your friend get 2 months free on your subscription. You can track your referrals and their status on the Referral Program page.";
"help_faq_q12" = "Which countries do you ship to?";
"help_faq_a12" = "We currently ship to Hungary, Slovakia, Czech Republic, Austria, Romania, Croatia, Spain, Italy, France, Germany, Norway, and Portugal. Domestic shipping within Hungary: {{huPostapoint}} (PostaPont) or {{huHome}} (home delivery). International shipping: {{intlPrice}} per order.";
"help_faq_q13" = "Can I have multiple pets on one account?";
"help_faq_a13" = "Yes. You can register multiple pets on a single account. Visit senra.pet for account details.";
"help_faq_q14" = "How do I report a found pet?";
"help_faq_a14" = "If the pet has a SENRA tag, simply scan the QR code with your phone's camera — no app needed. You can view the pet's profile and share your location with the owner.";
"help_faq_q15" = "Is my personal data safe?";
"help_faq_a15" = "Yes. You control exactly which data is visible when someone scans your pet's tag. In 'Settings' > 'Privacy Settings', you can choose whether to show your phone number, email address, or home address. Your login is protected by a one-time verification code every time — there's no password that could be stolen. You can delete your account and all your data at any time.";
"help_faq_q16" = "We lost the tag or it got damaged — what should I do?";
"help_faq_a16" = "Don't worry — your pet's digital profile is safe and is not stored on the tag. Go to the Account page and tap 'Order Replacement'. We'll link a new tag with a fresh QR code to your existing pet profile. Replacement eligibility depends on your Senra account; visit senra.pet for details. The old tag is deactivated immediately when the replacement is ordered.";
"help_faq_q17" = "My tag won't scan — what should I do?";
"help_faq_a17" = "Try the following: clean the tag surface with a damp cloth, ensure good lighting, hold your phone camera steadily about 10-15 cm from the tag, and check that your camera app or QR reader is working. If the QR code is scratched or worn, order a replacement from the 'Home/My Account' page.";
"help_faq_q18" = "I found a pet without a SENRA tag — what can I do?";
"help_faq_a18" = "Check the Missing Pets map on the SENRA website (senra.pet) — this pet may already have been reported missing in your area. You can also view missing pet alerts inside the app. Take the pet to the nearest vet clinic to have its microchip scanned. If the found pet has a SENRA tag, scan the QR code with your phone's camera — the owner's contact details will appear.";
"help_faq_q19" = "Can I change my email address?";
"help_faq_a19" = "Your primary email address serves as your account identifier and therefore cannot be changed directly. If you'd like to use a different email as your public contact, you can add a secondary email address in 'Settings' > 'Contact Details' — this can also appear on your pet's profile if you enable it, so the finder can see it immediately and contact you directly. If you absolutely need to change your primary email, contact us at hello@senra.pet and we'll help migrate your account.";
"help_faq_q20" = "What's the difference between a microchip and a SENRA QR tag?";
"help_faq_a20" = "A microchip is a tiny implant under your pet's skin that stores a unique 15-digit identifier — but it requires a special reader (usually only available at vets and shelters). The SENRA QR tag can be easily scanned with any smartphone camera, instantly displaying your pet's full profile, photo, and the contact details you've approved. The finder can also share where they found your pet.";
"help_faq_q21" = "What happens to my data if I cancel my subscription?";
"help_faq_a21" = "If you cancel your subscription, you retain access to paid features until the end of the current billing period. After that, your account automatically switches to the free Starter plan. Pet profiles, photos, and QR tags remain active — you only lose access to premium features (SMS notifications, vet alerts, free tag replacement, etc.). Your data is not deleted upon cancellation. To permanently delete all data, use the Delete Account option in Settings.";
"help_faq_q22" = "How can I register my clinic or shelter with SENRA?";
"help_faq_a22" = "Vet clinics and shelters can register at senra.pet/register-vet-shelter. Fill in the clinic or organisation details, and we'll send them a verification email. After confirmation, we'll automatically send them notifications when pets go missing in your area — helping lost pets get home. There's no cost and no login required.";
"help_faq_q23" = "How can I share a success story if my pet was found?";
"help_faq_a23" = "When you mark your pet as 'Found', we'll ask if you'd like to share the good news with others. You can publish a short story about how your pet was found. Public stories appear on the 'Found Pets' map. You can also publish or remove your pet's success story later by visiting their profile.";
"help_faq_q24" = "What browsers and devices are supported?";
"help_faq_a24" = "SENRA works on all browsers, including Chrome, Safari, Firefox, and Edge, on both mobile and desktop devices. QR tag scanning works with any smartphone camera — the finder doesn't need the SENRA app or even an account.";
"help_faq_q25" = "Can I order multiple tags for my pets at once?";
"help_faq_a25" = "Yes, you can order tags for all your pets at the same time. After the tags arrive, scan each one to activate it and assign it to the correct pet profile. You can also place additional orders at any time if you want to register more pets later.";
"help_faq_q26" = "How do missing pet alerts reach vets and shelters?";
"help_faq_a26" = "When you mark your pet as 'Missing', SENRA automatically sends email alerts to all registered vets and shelters in your area. This means local professionals are immediately aware that your pet is missing and can keep an eye out. The more vets and shelters registered in your area, the better this network works. You can help by encouraging your pet's vet to register on the SENRA website.";
"help_faq_q27" = "Can I transfer a tag to a different pet?";
"help_faq_a27" = "No. Every QR tag is permanently linked to one pet's profile. If a pet passes away or you no longer need the tag, the old tag simply becomes inactive. Order a new tag for your new pet on the SENRA website.";
"help_faq_q28" = "How can I register my pet's vet clinic or the shelter where I adopted my pet in the SENRA network?";
"help_faq_a28" = "Vet clinics and shelters can register at senra.pet/register-vet-shelter. Fill in the clinic or organisation details, and we'll send them a verification email. After confirmation, we'll automatically send them notifications when pets go missing in your area — helping lost pets get home sooner. There's no cost and no login required.";
