// Guide Items
"help_guide_qr_tags_title" = "QR Code Pet Tags";
"help_guide_qr_tags_desc" = "Each SENRA tag features a unique QR code that links to your pet's digital profile. Anyone who finds your pet can scan the code with their phone camera — no app download required. The scanner instantly sees your pet's photo, name, medical information, and your contact details. They can also share their GPS location with you so you know exactly where your pet is. Tags work with all modern smartphones.";
"help_guide_materials_title" = "Tag Materials & Durability";
"help_guide_materials_desc" = "SENRA tags are made from durable, lightweight metal with an epoxy coating for extra protection. They're waterproof and UV-resistant, suitable for all weather conditions. Tags attach securely to your pet's collar. If a tag becomes damaged or the QR code is no longer scannable, you can order a replacement from your Account page — free for Standard and Maximum plan members.";
"help_guide_emergency_title" = "Emergency Contact & Alerts";
"help_guide_emergency_desc" = "When someone scans your pet's tag, you receive an instant notification by email with the finder's location. Standard and Maximum plan members also receive SMS alerts for faster response. If you mark your pet as missing, a community alert is sent to all SENRA users within 10km, and registered vets and shelters in your area are also notified. Anyone in the community can report sightings with their location, building a trail to help you find your pet.";
"help_guide_profile_title" = "Pet Profile Management";
"help_guide_profile_desc" = "Your pet's digital profile is the heart of SENRA. Add essential details like name, species, breed, age, and a clear photo. You can also include medical information (allergies, medications, conditions), microchip number, and unique features that help identify your pet. Upload multiple photos to a gallery. All information can be updated at any time from the 'My Pets' section. You control which of your personal details (phone, email, address) are visible to people who scan the tag.";
"help_guide_missing_alerts_title" = "Missing Pet Alerts & Sightings";
"help_guide_missing_alerts_desc" = "If your pet goes missing, mark them as missing from 'My Pets' to create an instant community alert. Your pet's photo and details appear on the Missing Pets map visible to all SENRA users in your area. Community members can report sightings with their GPS location, which you receive as notifications. Registered vets and shelters are also alerted. Once your pet is found, mark them as found and optionally share your reunion story to inspire the community.";
"help_guide_community_title" = "Community & Found Pets";
"help_guide_community_desc" = "SENRA's strength is its community. The Missing Pets map shows active alerts near you — check it to see if any pets have been reported missing in your area. The Found Pets page celebrates successful reunions with stories from pet owners. You can register your local vet or animal shelter with SENRA so they receive missing pet alerts automatically, helping create a stronger safety network for all pets in your area.";
